        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes. Amplitude's Starter plan is completely free and includes 10,000 monthly tracked users, up to 2 million events, session replay, unlimited feature flags, web experimentation, and AI feedback. No credit card required to start.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Do I need coding skills to set up Amplitude?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Basic setup requires adding a JavaScript snippet to your site, which most people can do in minutes. Custom event tracking needs light coding, but Amplitude's Autotrack feature captures common interactions automatically. For deeper analysis, the visual query builder requires zero code.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How is Amplitude different from Google Analytics?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Google Analytics focuses on marketing attribution and pageviews. Amplitude is built for product analytics—it tracks user-level behavior, builds funnels around product actions, supports behavioral cohorts, includes session replay, and offers built-in experimentation. If you want to understand how people *use* your product (not just how they arrive), Amplitude is purpose-built for that.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
